  "texts": [
    "2000; Jager & Amblard 2005; Noorazar et al. 2020",
    "Thanks to the full history of user's interaction from our Twitter dataset, and assuming for the sake of simplicity that the functional form of µ, the opinion update function, is the same for all agents, we determined the most likely µ using symbolic regression.",
    "The regression was performed using genetic algorithms (Fortin et al. 2012) over the set F of arithmetic and trigonometric functions 7 as well as an implementation of the difference in the periodical opinion space.",
    "The output of the empirical calibration is a linear function of opinion updating",
    "We have thus demonstrated incidentally that this linear function, already widely used in the literature on opinion dynamics (Deffuant et al. 2000; Jager & Amblard 2005), is the one that best fits the empirical data among the set F when assuming an homogeneous functional form for the opinion fusion process."
  ],
